Light propagation in the CQDs functionalized tapered optical fiber is represented in the schematic figure (Fig. 9
                        ). Transmission spectra were monitored before and after the CQDs deposition as shown in Fig. 10
                        . The transmission spectra induce red shifts of 0.545 nm after CQDs functionalization. The longer red shift obtained for CQDs functionalized tapered optical fiber is due to optical interference at the tapered region in which the CQDs are successfully coated onto tapered optical fiber. Lower photon energy of light propagation in CQDs functionalized tapered optical fiber than non-CQDs functionalized tapered optical fiber is due to higher interface roughness of the surface [21,22].
